File cantera-1.6.0.tar.gz has been released.  If you are using Cantera 
on linux/unix/Mac OSX, I recommend that you upgrade to this release.  
On a Mac, I have verified that everything runs: 'make test' succeeds, 
and all Python and MATLAB demos run. Under linux, 'make test' succeeds 
and the Python demos work, but I currently do not have access to a 
linux machine with MATLAB installed, so I can't build and test the 
MATLAB toolbox.

Also, I have merged CVS branch 'Prerelease_1_6_0_branch' into the 
trunk.  So now simply executing 'cvs co cantera' will get version 
1.6.0.  If you are using Cantera from CVS, it may be simplest to check 
out a fresh working copy, rather than trying to update an old working 
copy. There is a delay at sourceforge in when these changes show up 
through anonymous CVS access, so wait until ~Monday to do this.  I have 
also tagged the current version as 'Release_1_6_0'.

Dave
